# Modal + DO secret sync

When touching deploy scripts, DO app specs, or CD workflows that materialize backend secrets:

## URL shape (blocking)

| Secret | Must | Must not |
|--------|------|----------|
| `VECINITA_MODAL_EMBED_URL` | `https://` base; host contains `vecinita--vecinita-embedding` | `fontface--` prefix; `/health` suffix |
| `VECINITA_MODAL_LLM_URL` | `https://` base; host contains `vecinita--vecinita-llm` | Same anti-patterns |

Validate with `scripts/deploy/modal_url_validate.py`. `do_apps.py` must call the validator
in `_apply_env_from_os` before any DO secret push.

## Sync parity (three places)

Any new backend secret must appear in **all** of:

1. `infra/do/<app>.yaml` (`type: SECRET`)
2. `scripts/deploy/do_apps.py` → `cmd_sync_secrets` key list
3. `scripts/deploy/sync_github_secrets.sh` `KEYS` (when CD deploys it)

Run `bash scripts/check_do_required_secrets.sh` after edits.

## Operator workflow

After Modal URL rotation or secret fix:

```bash
set -a && source prod.env && set +a
uv run --with pydo --with pyyaml scripts/deploy/do_apps.py sync-all-secrets
bash scripts/deploy/sync_github_secrets.sh --apply
bash scripts/infra/do_verify_required_secrets.sh
```

Skill: `.cursor/skills/do-secrets-sync/SKILL.md`.

Evidence: BUG-2026-07-01 — wrong `fontface--` embed URL on internal-write-api caused eval 404.
